ntral European University Press, 2004) [https://web.archive.org/web/20120210024250/http://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=115015309 online edition]\n* Williams, Charles. ''Adenauer: The Father of the New Germany'' (2000) [https://www.questia.com/library/106754929/adenauer-the-father-of-the-new-germany Online]\n\n===Primary sources===\n* Beate Ruhm Von Oppen, ed. ''Documents on Germany under Occupation, 1945\u20131954'' (Oxford University Press, 1955) [https://www.questia.com/library/407620/documents-on-germany-under-occupation-1945-1954 online]\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category-inline|West Germany}}\n\n{{Germany topics}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:West Germany| ]]\n[[Category:Contemporary German history]]\n[[Category:Former polities of the Cold War]]\n[[Category:Anti-communism in Germany]]\n[[Category:Borders of Germany]]\n[[Category:Political history of Germany]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1949]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1990]]\n[[Category:1949 establishments in Germany|*]]\n[[Category:1990 disestablishments in Germany|*]]\n[[Category:1949 establishments in West Germany|*]]\n[[Category:1990 disestablishments in West Germany|*]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the Federal Republic of Germany as it was between 1949 and 1990 (the Bonn Republic)|the Federal Republic of Germany since 1990 (the Berlin Republic)|Germany|the German state between 1919 and 1933 (the Weimar Republic)|Weimar Republic}}\n{{distinguish|Old states of Germany|Western Germany}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{short description|Federal Republic of Germany from 1949 to 1990}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox country\n<!--\n|_noautocat = yes\n|country = Germany\n|states = 10\n|flag = Flag of West Germany#Divided Germany (1949\u201389)\n|continent = Europe\n-->\n| conventional_long_name = <span style=\"line-height:1.33em;\">Federal Republic of Germany</span>\n| native_name = <span style=\"line-height:1.33em;\">{{lang|de|Bundesrepublik Deuts